main event: On September 14, 1965, an observer sighted an oval-shaped silver object in Lyons, Kansas.
interesting points: The object was reported to have been visible for 5 to 7 minutes., A total of 4 witnesses were noted, including Mr. E.D. Billingsby and Ernest Gustafson., The report had insufficient data to draw definitive conclusions about the object., No physical evidence of the sighting was obtained., The investigation was part of Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program.
